node.text: Simone Biles is celebrating Team USA's silver medal victory. ❤️ "I'm SO proud of these girls right here. You girls are incredibly brave & talented! I'll forever be inspired by your determination to not give up and to fight through adversity! They stepped up when I couldn't," Biles wrote. "Thanks for being there for me and having my back! Forever love y'all." 🙏 | 📷: Laurence Griffiths/Getty Images

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by People Magazine on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Wentworth Miller is sharing his autism diagnosis with the world. 🙏 The Prison Break actor revealed that he was diagnosed with autism as an adult last year, telling his followers, "This isn't something I'd change … immediately being autistic is central to who I am. To everything I've achieved/articulated." Miller noted that "access to a diagnosis is a privilege many do not enjoy," admitting that his diagnosis was "a shock," but "not a surprise." He ended his message by thanking those who "consciously or unconsciously gave me that extra bit of grace + space over the years" and allowed him to "move thru the world in a way that made sense to me whether or not it made sense to them." Tap the bio link for more. | 📷: Splash

node.text: Filipina weightlifter Hidilyn Diaz keeps making history at the Summer Olympics. 👏 Diaz triumphed in the women's 55kg event, and her gold is the first-ever for her country. "It's unbelievable," she said afterward. "I expected to win, but when you hold this already, it's like, 'Wow, I never thought this would happen today.'" Tap the bio link for her story. | 📷: Brendan Moran/Sportsfile/Getty, Chris Graythen/Getty, VINCENZO PINTO/AFP via Getty Images

node.text: Simone Biles said she is "dealing with some things internally" after her early exit from the women's gymnastics team final. 🙏  Though she did not win gold, Biles said she was "proud" of how the rest of the team performed, earning second place behind the Russians. "I'm proud for how the girls stepped up and did what they had to do. I owe this to the girls, it has nothing to do with me," she said. "I am very proud of them." ❤️ Tap the bio link for more. | 📷: Laurence Griffiths/Getty Images

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by People Magazine on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text: Simone Biles, Suni Lee, Jordan Chiles and Grace McCallum won silver in the women's team all-around final at the Tokyo Summer Olympics. At Tuesday's final, Lee, Chiles and McCallum carried on with the competition after their veteran captain Biles suddenly exited the floor after the vault, which was her first apparatus and her signature event. Tap the bio link for more. | 📷: Laurence Griffiths/Getty Images

node.text: In a surprise reversal of her Tokyo Olympic hopes, Simone Biles exited the women's gymnastics team finals early on Tuesday night in Japan — after briefly leaving the competition floor following a botched showing in the vault event. Tap the bio link for the full story. | 📷: Jamie Squire/Getty Images

node.text: Lauren Burnham Luyendyk is on the mend after being hospitalized for a severe case of mastitis. 🙏 The former Bachelor contestant is back home and "feeling much better," her husband, Arie Luyendyk Jr., shared. Lauren also posted a video cuddling Lux, captioning the post: "back home where I get to snuggle these little squooshes." ❤️ Tap the bio link for more. | #Regram @ariejr

node.text: The final victim has been recovered from site of the devastating Surfside, Florida condo collapse that killed 98 people last month. Estelle Hedaya, who lived in the Champlain Towers South condo that fell in the early morning hours of June 24, has finally been pulled from the debris, her brother Ikey Hedaya confirmed. Tap the link in bio for more details. 📷: Facebook
